The Northwest APC Social Media Forum has commended Senator representing Kaduna Central, Uba Sani for what it described as the giant strides of the lawmaker through the sponsorship of eight “people-oriented” legislative bills despite being a first-time Senator. Chairman of the Forum, Ahmed Rufai Gumel,made the commendation during a tour of Jigawa State for inspection of Federal Government’s educational intervention in Sule Lamido University, Kafin Hausa. The Forum stated that Uba Sani, who is also the Chairman Senate Committee on Banking, Insurance and other Financial Institutions, “has an impressive record of empowerment for youth, women and children, especially in his Constituency”. The group noted that his “unwavering war on poverty, by ensuring massive access to Federal Government’s SMEs and providing scholarships for indigent students in his Constituency,” is a thing of pride for the North. Representatives from Kaduna State at the inspection tour included Aminu Wazeery, Ismaeel Kasim and Nasir Babanyaya. The Forum also visited the Integrated Power Project at Gujungu and Irrigation Water Project to boost farming at Auyo in Jigawa State. It then commended Senator Uba Sani for appointing its Youth Leader, Ismaeel Kasim as one of his aides. The Forum’s leadership also held closed-door meetings with the acting National Chairman of APC, Governor Mai Mala Buni and the Secretary to the Government of Federation, Boss Mustapha in Abuja.